      "TriggersInbound.TriggerInputMappingProperty": {
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "description": "Input mapping property configuration for extracting values from webhook payload.\n\nEach property can independently use code or LLM for extraction.\n",
        "properties": {
          "extraction_instructions": {
            "description": "Instructions for extracting the property value from the webhook payload.\n\nFor type: json_path - A JSONPath expression that specifies the path to extract from the webhook payload.\nJSONPath is a query language for JSON, similar to XPath for XML. The expression should point to the value(s)\nto extract. If the path matches multiple values, only the first match will be used.\n\nJSONPath syntax examples:\n- `$.user.email` - Extract the email field from a nested user object\n- `$.items[0].name` - Extract the name from the first item in an items array\n- `$.data.price` - Extract the price from a nested data object\n- `$['user-name']` - Extract a field with special characters (use brackets notation)\n\nFor type: code - Python code that:\n- Reads from the `data` variable (the webhook payload)\n- Sets the extracted value to the `result` variable\n- Returns None if the value cannot be extracted\n- The `data` variable is deep-copied for each extraction, so mutations are safe\n- For update/upsert actions on non-primary-key fields: `current_value` variable is available\n  containing the existing entity's current value for this property (None if entity doesn't exist or value wasn't set before)\n\n## Available Variables\n\n- `data`: The webhook payload (dict/object)\n- `current_value`: Current entity value (only for non-primary-key fields in update/upsert)\n- `property`: Target property metadata (dict) always contains:\n  - `name`: Property name (str)\n  - `type`: Property type (str) - \"text\", \"number\", \"select\", \"json\", \"file\", \"url\", etc.\n  - `subtype`: Property subtype (str or None) - \"single_select\", \"multi_select\", etc.\n  - `config`: Property configuration (dict, empty for most types)\n    - For select properties: `options` (list[str]) - available option values\n    - For select properties: `max_selected` (int or None) - maximum selectable options\n\n## Return Format by Property Type\n\n### Text, Number, URL Properties\n```python\n# Return as string or None\nresult = data.get('user_name')  # \"John Doe\"\nresult = data.get('price')      # \"42.5 USD\"\nresult = data.get('url')        # \"https://example.com\"\n```\n\n### JSON Property\n```python\n# Return as dict/list/primitive or None\nresult = data.get('metadata')   # {\"key\": \"value\"}\nresult = data.get('items')      # [1, 2, 3]\n# System will automatically stringify to JSON\n```\n\n### Select Property\n```python\n# Return as list of strings or None\nresult = [\"Option1\", \"Option2\"]\n# For single value: [\"Option1\"]\n# String format also accepted: \"Option1\"\n```\n\n### File Property\n```python\n# Return as dict with file_url or file_base64, or as string URL\nresult = {\"file_url\": \"https://example.com/doc.pdf\", \"file_name\": \"doc.pdf\"}\n# Or simpler: result = \"https://example.com/doc.pdf\"\n```\n\nExamples (code):\n```python\n# Simple field access\nresult = data.get('user_name')\n\n# Nested field access\nresult = data.get('user', {}).get('email')\n\n# Array access\nresult = data.get('items', [])[0].get('id') if data.get('items') else None\n\n# Conditional extraction\nif data.get('status') == 'active':\n    result = data.get('user_id')\nelse:\n    result = None\n\n# Using current_value for updates (only available for non-primary-key fields in update/upsert actions)\n# Preserve existing value if new value is not provided\nresult = data.get('description') if data.get('description') is not None else current_value\n\n# Append to existing value\nnew_tag = data.get('tag')\nif new_tag and current_value:\n    result = f\"{current_value}, {new_tag}\"\nelif new_tag:\n    result = new_tag\nelse:\n    result = current_value\n\n# Using property metadata - fuzzy matching for select properties\n# property = {\"name\": \"Status\", \"type\": \"select\", \"subtype\": \"single_select\",\n#             \"config\": {\"options\": [\"Pending\", \"Approved\", \"Rejected\"]}}\nstatus_input = data.get('status', '').lower()\nif property.get('type') == 'select':\n    # Fuzzy match input to available options (case-insensitive)\n    available_options = property.get('config', {}).get('options', [])\n    for option in available_options:\n        if option.lower() == status_input:\n            result = [option]\n            break\n    else:\n        # No match found\n        result = None\nelse:\n    result = data.get('status')\n\n# Multi-select with max_selected validation\n# property = {\"type\": \"select\", \"subtype\": \"multi_select\",\n#             \"config\": {\"options\": [...], \"max_selected\": 3}}\n# Note: max_selected can be None (no limit)\ntags_input = data.get('tags', [])\nif property.get('type') == 'select':\n    available = property['config']['options']\n    max_opts = property['config']['max_selected']\n\n    # Filter to only valid options\n    valid_tags = [tag for tag in tags_input if tag in available]\n\n    # Respect max_selected limit if set\n    if max_opts and len(valid_tags) > max_opts:\n        valid_tags = valid_tags[:max_opts]\n\n    result = valid_tags if valid_tags else None\n```\n\nFor type: llm - Natural language prompt describing what to extract, e.g.:\n\"Extract the user's email address from the payload\"\n\nFor type: json_path - Examples:\n```\n$.user.email\n$.items[0].id\n$.data.nested.value\n$['field-with-dash']\n```\n",
            "example": "result = data.get('user', {}).get('email')",
            "minLength": 3,
            "type": "string"
          },
          "primary_key": {
            "description": "Whether to use the values of that property to find pre-existing entities for update or upsert operations.\n\nIMPORTANT for update_entity actions:\n- Primary key properties can be non-manual (computed) properties - they're used for matching existing entities only\n- Non-manual primary keys are automatically excluded from the update payload (their values won't be changed)\n- All other properties (non-primary keys and all properties in create_entity/upsert_entity) must be manual\n",
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "target_property_id": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Common.UUID"
          },
          "type": {
            "description": "Extraction method: code (Python), llm (natural language prompt), or json_path (JSONPath expression)",
            "enum": [
              "code",
              "llm",
              "json_path"
            ],
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "target_property_id",
          "primary_key",
          "type",
          "extraction_instructions"
        ],
        "title": "TriggersInbound.TriggerInputMappingProperty",
        "type": "object"
      },
