      "Skills.UpdateCodeSkillRequest": {
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "description": "Update a code skill. For generated skills (where generated=true), the following\nfields act as overrides:\n- name, description, code, dependencies, allowed_domains, additional_prompt\n\nOverride behavior for generated skills:\n- Setting a field to a value creates an override\n- Setting a field to null explicitly clears the override (reverts to generated value)\n- Setting a field to the same value as generated data is treated as clearing the override\n\nFor non-generated skills, required fields (name, description, code) cannot be set to null.\n",
        "properties": {
          "allowed_domains": {
            "description": "Domains the skill can make requests to. For generated skills, set to null to revert to generated value.",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Skills.Domain"
            },
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "array"
          },
          "code": {
            "description": "Python code for the skill execution. Must contain a `run()` function as the entry point.\nThe function signature will be automatically analyzed to extract parameter schema.\nUse type annotations to specify parameter types and descriptions.\n\nFor secrets, use Secret(\"secret_name\") to reference secrets configured via /secrets APIs.\nFor files, use Annotated[File, \"description\"] to accept file uploads.\nFor regular parameters, use Annotated[type, \"description\"].\n\nExample:\n```python\nfrom typing import Annotated\nimport requests\n\ndef run(api_key: Annotated[str, Secret(\"gmail_api_key\")],\n        input_file: Annotated[File, \"CSV file to process\"],\n        to_email: Annotated[str, \"Recipient email address\"]) -> str:\n    # Implementation here\n    with open(input_file) as f:\n        data = f.read()\n    return \"File processed and email sent successfully\"\n```\n\n\nFor generated skills: set to null to revert to the original generated code.\n",
            "example": "import requests\nfrom typing import Annotated\n\ndef run(api_key: Annotated[str, Secret(\"gmail_api_key\")],\n        to_email: Annotated[str, \"Recipient email address\"],\n        subject: Annotated[str, \"Email subject\"]):\n    # Send email using the secret API key\n    # api_key will be automatically injected from workspace secrets\n    response = requests.post(\n        \"https://api.gmail.com/send\",\n        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\"},\n        json={\"to\": to_email, \"subject\": subject}\n    )\n    return {\"status\": \"sent\", \"message_id\": response.json()[\"id\"]}\n",
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "string"
          },
          "dependencies": {
            "description": "List of Python dependencies. For generated skills, set to null to revert to generated value.",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Skills.Dependency"
            },
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "array"
          },
          "description": {
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "string"
          },
          "type": {
            "enum": [
              "code"
            ],
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "type"
        ],
        "title": "Skills.UpdateCodeSkillRequest",
        "type": "object"
      },
      "AgentSkills.CreateAgentSkillRequest": {
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "properties": {
          "alias": {
            "description": "Short human-readable alias. If omitted, will be auto-generated.",
