      "TriggersInbound.TriggerRowSplitter.WithInstructions": {
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "description": "Row splitter with instructions - split webhook payload into multiple rows using code or LLM.\n\nFor code type: Python code that reads from `data` (the webhook payload) and assigns to `result` an array of payloads.\nEach item in the result array represents one row and should be a dictionary/object with the same structure as the original payload.\n\nFor llm type: Natural language prompt describing how to split the payload.\n",
        "properties": {
          "instructions": {
            "description": "For type: code - Python code that:\n- Reads from the `data` variable (the webhook payload)\n- Sets `result` to a list of dictionaries (one per row)\n- Each dictionary should have the same structure as the original payload\n- Returns empty list if no rows should be created\n\nIMPORTANT: Keep the payload structure identical to the original. This allows you to add or remove\nthe row splitter later without updating downstream property extraction code. Copy shared data\n(like metadata, timestamps, etc.) into each row, and only vary the row-specific data.\n\nExample (code) - Splitting spreadsheet cell updates into separate rows:\n```python\n# Input payload structure:\n# {\n#   \"updates\": [\n#     {\"cell\": \"A1\", \"value\": \"John\", \"sheet\": \"Contacts\"},\n#     {\"cell\": \"A2\", \"value\": \"Jane\", \"sheet\": \"Contacts\"}\n#   ],\n#   \"spreadsheet\": {\"id\": \"abc123\", \"name\": \"CRM Data\"},\n#   \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n# }\n\nresult = []\nfor update in data.get('updates', []):\n    # Create a row with the same structure, varying only the update-specific data\n    row = {\n        'updates': [update],  # Single update per row\n        'spreadsheet': data.get('spreadsheet'),  # Copy shared metadata\n        'timestamp': data.get('timestamp')  # Copy shared timestamp\n    }\n    result.append(row)\n\n# Result: Each row maintains the original structure, downstream extraction code\n# like \"result = data.get('updates', [])[0].get('value')\" works with or without splitter\n```\n\nExample (code) - Simple array splitting:\n```python\n# If payload is just an array of items\nresult = data.get('items', [])\n```\n\nFor type: llm - Natural language prompt describing how to split the payload, e.g.:\n\"Split the payload into separate rows, one for each update in the 'updates' array\"\n",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "type": {
            "enum": [
              "code",
              "llm"
            ],
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "type",
          "instructions"
        ],
        "title": "TriggersInbound.TriggerRowSplitter.WithInstructions",
        "type": "object"
      },
