      "TriggersInbound.TriggerSimplifiedDeploymentDefinition.MatcherDefinition": {
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "description": "Matcher definition for identifying existing entities in update/upsert actions.\n\nMatchers extract values from the webhook payload and compare them against stored values\non target entities to find matches. When a match is found, the entity is updated instead\nof creating a new one.\n\nMultiple matchers are combined with AND logic - all matchers must match for an entity to be found.\nIf a matcher extracts `null` (value not found in payload), that matcher is skipped during matching.\nIf ALL matchers extract `null`, no entity will be matched.\n",
        "properties": {
          "extraction_instructions": {
            "description": "Instructions for extracting the matcher value from the webhook payload.\n\n## For type: json_path\n\nA JSONPath expression that specifies the path to extract from the webhook payload.\nJSONPath is a query language for JSON, similar to XPath for XML. If the path matches\nmultiple values, only the first match will be used.\n\nJSONPath syntax examples:\n- `$.order_id` - Extract the order_id field from root\n- `$.user.email` - Extract the email from a nested user object\n- `$.items[0].id` - Extract the id from the first item in an array\n- `$.data.customer.id` - Extract deeply nested value\n- `$['field-with-dash']` - Extract a field with special characters (use brackets notation)\n\n## For type: code\n\nPython code that extracts a value from the webhook payload.\n\n### Available Variables\n\n- `data`: The webhook payload (dict/object) - a deep copy, so mutations are safe\n\n### How to Extract\n\nSet the `result` variable to the extracted value. The system automatically wraps your\nresult - you just need to extract the raw value:\n\n```python\n# Simple field access\nresult = data.get('order_id')\n\n# Nested field access\nresult = data.get('customer', {}).get('id')\n\n# Array access with safety\nitems = data.get('items', [])\nresult = items[0].get('sku') if items else None\n\n# Conditional extraction\nif data.get('type') == 'order':\n    result = data.get('order_number')\nelse:\n    result = data.get('reference_id')\n\n# Combining multiple fields\nfirst = data.get('first_name', '')\nlast = data.get('last_name', '')\nresult = f\"{first} {last}\".strip() if (first or last) else None\n\n# Extract from nested arrays\nresult = None\nfor item in data.get('line_items', []):\n    if item.get('primary'):\n        result = item.get('product_id')\n        break\n```\n\nIf `result` is `None` or not set, the matcher is skipped during entity matching.\n\n## For type: llm\n\nNatural language prompt describing what value to extract from the payload.\nThe AI will analyze the payload structure and extract the requested value.\n\nExamples:\n- \"Extract the customer's unique identifier\"\n- \"Find the order reference number\"\n- \"Get the primary email address from the contact information\"\n- \"Extract the transaction ID or reference code\"\n",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "type": {
            "description": "Extraction method:\n- `json_path`: JSONPath expression for direct value extraction\n- `code`: Python code for complex extraction logic\n- `llm`: Natural language description for AI-powered extraction\n",
            "enum": [
              "code",
              "llm",
              "json_path"
            ],
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "type",
          "extraction_instructions"
        ],
        "title": "TriggersInbound.TriggerSimplifiedDeploymentDefinition.MatcherDefinition",
        "type": "object"
      },
