    "/api/workspaces/{workspace_id}/projects/{project_id}/triggers/inbound/{inbound_trigger_id}/enable": {
      "post": {
        "callbacks": {},
        "deprecated": true,
        "description": "**Deprecated**: Use `/source` instead.\n\nEnables the trigger (sets status to active) with provider configuration.\n\nWhen enabled, webhooks create entities in the backing project automatically.\n\n## Provider Configuration Options\n\n1. **Set Pipedream provider**: `{\"provider\": \"pipedream\", \"provider_metadata\": {\"trigger_id\": \"...\", \"external_user_id\": \"...\"}}`\n   - Requires both trigger_id and external_user_id in provider_metadata\n   - Verifies the deployed trigger exists in Pipedream\n   - Deletes remote Pipedream trigger on trigger deletion\n\n2. **Set Other/Custom provider**: `{\"provider\": \"other\"}`\n   - No metadata required for custom webhooks\n\n3. **Preserve existing configuration**: `{}` (empty request body)\n   - Re-enables trigger with previously configured provider settings\n   - Returns error if no provider was previously configured\n   - Useful for re-activating a disabled trigger without changing its configuration\n",
        "operationId": "inbound-trigger-enable",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "description": "",
            "in": "path",
            "name": "workspace_id",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Common.UUID"
            }
          },
          {
            "description": "",
            "in": "path",
            "name": "project_id",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Common.UUID"
            }
          },
          {
            "description": "",
            "in": "path",
            "name": "inbound_trigger_id",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Common.UUID"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
